util.alg

Interface Monoid<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MonoidProvider, StreamMonoid

    public interface Monoid<T>
    Classes implementing this interface state that T-values are the objects of a monoid. Consequently an implementing class provides both the binary operation and identity that make the T-values into a monoid. Methods in this interface are named with multiplicative notation in mind: the binary operation is the "product" and the identity is the "unit".
